column5: Was doing some night trolling with my brother for walleye when this nice musky grabbed his 3-4 inch crank...  No tape on it cause I didn't have my musky gear...  But she was big... Not 50 inches but not far off... I guessed at 48
Sweet
Gives OOPS, a whole new meaning Dont tell me you got that on 10lb PP
Yup...  Almost spooled him... We had to chase it with the boat...
Awesome Should send that pic to them.Maybe get some freebies
I did an oops to yesterday fishing for walleye too!  Your fish was much bigger though!!
Nothing gets the ole ticker fired up quite as much as night time muskies !!  Goodun Mike !!
Where was the walleye you were targeting, inside the muskie? Very nice fish!
Sometimes an accident is a good thing.
We let them go last night...  But we didn't get any where we got the musky... For obvious reasons...
Well that's the nicest "Oops" I've ever seen!!  Well Done!
Crazy. Nice surprise Im sure.
Well done !
sounds like me on Sat.  12LB nanofil on my med action jigging rod right as it got dark.  I'll post a report rather then say more here.  Nice "ooops"!!!
Very nice Mike I hope it was from a area you don't target musky so it gave you a new place to look for them.
Kinda...  A new spot on the spot if you will...
Wow, congrats to him on landing that on 10lb PP!
sweet fish - that would be a blast bringing in on a walleye setup- well done on keeping it on
I had a couple oops too this weekend but they didn't end so well.  I got bit off twice! Hey he didn't have my lures did he by any chance?   Nice fish!
Hoochy Mama......that's one big walleye...  ...NICE FISH...you're taking some of these OLD TIMER musky anglers to night school...  Musky Mike is the MAN....
i think im just blabbing more....  :blahblah1:  trying to keep you guys entertained...  :clapping:
It's NOT blabbing when you can back it up.....
